Merkel Defends Germany’s Export Surplus, Stuttgarter Reports

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-02-22T05:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/merkel-defends-germany-s-export-surplus-stuttgarter-reports.html
German  Chancellor Angela Merkel  said
the country’s competitive edge in certain areas and its
resulting export surplus shouldn’t be eliminated by regulation,
 Stuttgarter Zeitung  reported, citing an interview.  Countries in the euro area should strive to match the best
performers and  Germany  is the “benchmark” in a number of
areas, Merkel said, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  